description:
The people of Manhattan struggle to survive the final hours of the Skrull invasion. But if they do survive, is there a world left for them to live in?

Ben Urich and a new friend witness the climatic battle in Central Park.
name: Chapter Five: Dark Reign

description: Would you destroy the world, if it was your only chance to save it? No, not this world. A dark, twisted, miserable version of this world—one that shouldn’t even exist. One that won’t exist, if you succeed. That’s the choice Lucas Bishop had to make it—and he’d make it again, in a heartbeat. He’s been captured by X-Force, but it’s all part of the plan. And while Cyclops thinks he’s finally removed the only threat to the Cable and the mutant messiah child out in the timestream, he couldn’t be more wrong. He’s only made it worse.
name: Waiting For The End of the World, Chapter Three - Little Triggers

description: Iceman continues his westward saga. Can everyone’s favorite, frigid X-Man survive Mystique’s kiss of death? And if so, will he ever be the same again? Also featuring Nightcrawler and Mercury in tales of mischief.
name: Kill or Cure, Part 4; Mercury; Work it out

description:
It's a double-sized sci-fi spectacular, guest-starring the Lady Liberators (fresh from the pages of The Hulk) and the female heroes from the Guardians of the Galaxy! When She-Hulk finds herself suddenly transported off-world, it’s up to her and a collection of the universe’s most powerful heroines including Storm, Thundra, Valkyre and the Invisible Woman - to figure out what’s going on…before a brand-new foe annihilates them!

This issue is noteworthy for being the first time since the cancellation of Captain Marvel vol. 4/5 that Phylla-Vell / Quasar has been written by her creator, Peter David.

A thousand years ago in a faraway galaxy a race of people discovered an enormous source of energy. They incorporated it into their world. But soon, it matured into something even more powerful and an infinite number of times more destructive.

This tremedously terrifying force came to be called Daemonstorm, because of its many properties... among them being quakes, violent storms, gravitational surges and even mutated and violent living creatures.

These people conditioned a race of ultimate soldiers called StormWalkers to combat the Storm. This is the end of their story. And the beginning of a new one...

volume.name: Dutch Decker And The Voodoo Queen

description:
A sword so magical that it’s name has gone into the legends of myth and fable as one of the most revered weapons ever. But it symbolized much more than just a steel blade, it was the symbol of the great King…of the Round Table…of the nobility of the Knights…of the magic of Camelot.

Excalibur.

The tale of Arthur’s magical sword, Excalibur that this is not the romanticized King Arthur of popular belief, but more of the traditional and historical view.
name: Excalibur

description: Lori finds herself trapped in the grind of low budget flicks and exploitative directors. Mired with the passion of stardom, but lacking in talent, Lori constantly hopes for her big break. When Dick Van Von, a producer known for films of the occult teams up with the sadistic rock star wannabee, Natasha Reich and utilizes the forbidden book of the Necronomicon, Lori finds herself plunged into a world of betrayal, deception, mayhem, redemption and deliverance. Now, she becomes the lead actress of a real life adventure co-starring with demons, timid heroes, and a lustful sorcerer.

While finishing up her degree in occult sciences in London, former actress Lori Lovecraft meets one of her idols, the famous actor Sir Andrew Parke-Jones. He invites her to his estate in Scotland to view his collection of esoteric lore, but when she arrives Sir Andrew has suffered a fatal heart attack. Eccentric Zelda brings Lori to her lab at Voodoo Mansion where she introduces Lori to her boyfriend/science experiment, Horatio, who has been lying sedated under the customized coffin-nosed hood of the Cord. Lori discovers that Voodoo Mansion isn't quite in the real world and discovers Sir Andrew now alive, hale and hearty. And if that wasn't enough, a mysterious Dark Lady appears and her only goal is to terrorize Lori in this surreal landscape...
name: The Dark Lady

description: Story and Art by Michael Larson. Cover by Kyle Kieliszewski. 64 pages B&W

We have excess of extra 'M's so: This month starts with a mountain of massively malevolent mayhem from the minds of Mark Waid (52, CAPTAIN AMERICA) and Marcos Martin (DR. STRANGE: THE OATH). With Spidey trapped underground, the Web-Head learns more about the surprising new cast-member who promises to cause trouble for him and his old pall JJJ.
name: Unscheduled Stop, Part 2

description: She wrote down everything. Her lovers were powerful men and when she threatened to go public with it, she died. Murdered? Possibly. But the diary went missing. The woman was Marilyn Monroe and her lovers included J.F.K.. Her death remains a mystery...as does the Red Diary as it has never turned up anywhere...until now...along with more diaries that chronicle a dark chapter in American history. Assassination, cover-ups, conspiracy and more are revealed as an investigative team find themselves caught in the 40 year old maelstrom when a man claims to have the secret diary kept by Marilyn Monroe. The secrets it has, along with additional diaries, can blow open the whole scandal that involved among other things the assassination of John F. Kennedy. A conspiracy of secrets...a conspiracy of murder.
name: The Red Diaries

description:
Should not be confused with the Superior Junk Comics' Tapestry title.

Collects:

THE WALLAS

DREAMWALKER

BURRITO, JACK-OF-ALL-TRADES

THE ADVENTURES OF SIMONE & AJAX

The investigative team searches for clues about a mysterious man's claim that the Red Diaries kept by Marilyn Monroe revealed secrets that would lead not only to her murderer, but the truth behind the assassination of President John F. Kennedy. Even though skeptical, the investigators find out that the matter is much more serious and deadlier than they ever expected, even after all this time.

The conspiracy laden mini-series continues as the investigative team find the deeper they dig, the more questions and less answers appear. They also discover that asking the right questions but to the wrong people can have deadly consequences. The informant Carlos stuns with his revelations about the secret between JFK and Marilyn Monroe.

The shocking conclusion to this conspiracy mini-series about JFK and Marilyn Monroe! Tragedy strikes the team as one of their key members falls and the enveloping conspiracy wraps them all in danger with little hope of finding the truth.

Spinning from the World Wide Web straight to your spinner rack! Based on this summer's blockbuster films, Iron Man and The Incredible Hulk, Marvel is proud to present two stories previously available only on Marvel.Com, plus an all-new chapter from the Marvel Movieverse, not seen anywhere yet!

Iron Man: Fast Friends brings insight into the bond between Tony 'Iron Man' Stark and James 'I'm in the Air Force' Rhodes, and why they're such good buddies. The Incredible Hulk: The Fury Files features SHIELD director Nick Fury figuring out why it's a bad idea to make Bruce Banner angry.
name: Iron Man: Fast Friends;  Incredible Hulk: The Fury Files;  Nick Fury: Spies Like Us

description:
"The coroner's men flipped the redheaded corpse over so Dukes and Magnus from Homicide could get a better look at her. 'Better' being a relative term in this case, with the claw marks that slashed her face into a featureless, bloody mask and turned her guts into a butcher shop explosion.

"But the tattoo -- the simple, encircled 'X' above the left shoulder blade -- remained intact, and Dukes pointed it out with the toe of his wingtip once Peter the rookie was done heaving up lunch.

"'See this ink?' he said. 'Means she did time at this reform school upstate, run by this shrink, Xavier...'"

description: We all remember when the Scarlet Witch uttered the three words that would change the landscape of the Marvel Universe: “No More Mutants!” But what if she said something different? And what of the consequences…? In a world without great power, who bears the burden of responsibility? Who will stand up to an enemy who fills the vacuum of power and whose hatred is unparalleled? Brian Reed (SECRET INVASION: FRONT LINE) with Marvel's own Jim McCann and brand-spankin’ new artist Paolo Pantalena answer the question: "What if Scarlet Witch had ended the HOUSE OF M by saying "NO MORE POWERS!" Also featuring Part 1 of a special five part back-up story in all the What Ifs this year, in which we see Iron Lad take a different path that leads him to recruit a different set of future Avengers. Join C.B. Cebulski (X-MEN: DIVIDED WE STAND, LONERS) and Patrick Spaziante (MUTIES, Sonic The Hedgehog) as they ask, 'What if the Runaways Became the Young Avengers?'
name: What If... Scarlet Witch Ended The "House Of M" By Saying "No More Powers"?;  What If... Runaways Became The Young Avengers? Part 1 Of 5

description:
Jackie is back in the US, but he's no longer the wielder of the The Darkness. In order to regain his status, he is working in some decent jobs like gunrunning. While slaughtering a local gang, Jackie was interrupted by Aphrodite IV, who was last seen testing her abilities against Sara Pezzini in New York.

Without the powers of the Darkness, what chances does Jackie has against this gorgeous assassin? And maybe more important, what is the organization she works for planning to do with Estacado?
name: Crooked, Part 1
